<body>
    <h1>2=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 REST and the Swagger Specification</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p></p>
<div class=3D"">
<div class=3D"childtabs-macro" data-fixed-position=3D"false">
<div class=3D"aui-tabs horizontal-tabs" data-aui-responsive=3D"true">
<strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data-conte=
nt-id=3D"1203279299">Introduction to REST</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"994375ee-4ef4-42a9-911e-c52452d1=
d891-1203279299">
<h3 id=3D"IntroductiontoREST-WhatisREST(RepresentationalStateTransfer)?">Wh=
at is REST (Representational State Transfer)?</h3>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"117" src=3D"11a0e998bc0b0cf3a6c71c49a5c41ab9436518d3a4ad1c922c84dcf59f=
9b418c" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279299/image2021-11-22_=
13-21-35.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571073880&amp;api=3Dv2"=
 data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279301"=
 data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment=
" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-22_13-21-35.png" data-=
base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-con=
tent-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279299" da=
ta-linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" alt=3D"" width=3D"321"></span></=
p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">REST (REpresentational State Trans=
fer) is<span>&nbsp;</span></span><em>an architectural style</em><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span>for designing networked appli=
cations. The term was coined by Roy Fielding in 2000 in his now-famous PhD =
dissertation<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"ht=
tp://www.ics.uci.edu/~fielding/pubs/dissertation/rest_arch_style.htm" style=
=3D"text-decoration: none;" rel=3D"nofollow">Architectural Styles and the D=
esign of Network-based Software Architectures</a><span style=3D"color: rgb(=
23,43,77);">. The REST architectural style has been used to guide the desig=
n and development of the architecture for the modern Web and thus is based =
on HTTP concepts.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">The 3 core concepts in REST are: r=
esources, methods (verbs) and response codes.</span></p>
<h3 id=3D"IntroductiontoREST-WhatisaRESTfulAPI?">What is a RESTful API?</h3=
>
<p>Conforming to the REST constraints is generally referred to as being =E2=
=80=9CRESTful=E2=80=9D.</p>
<p>Complying with these constraints, and thus conforming to the REST archit=
ectural style enables any kind of distributed hypermedia system to have des=
irable emergent properties, such as performance, scalability, simplicity, m=
odifiability, visibility, portability, and reliability.</p>
<p>The key components of REST are: resources, actions and response codes. R=
esources are used to encapsulate the information to be processed and are re=
presented in the form of URIs (eg. <a href=3D"http://api.example.com/custom=
ers" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http://api.example.com/custom=
ers</a>). Actions are represented as HTTP methods (verbs) which include GET=
, PUT, POST, DELETE and are used to indicate the nature of processing requi=
red. Response codes indicate whether processing was successful or not; typi=
cal response codes are 200 (Ok), 400 (Bad Request), 404 (Not Found), 500 (I=
nternal Server Error).</p>
<p>Key points for successfully offering a RESTful API are:</p>
<ul>
<li>Use HTTP Verbs as intended in RFC7231</li>
<li>Provide sensible resource names</li>
<li>Use HTTP response codes to indicate status</li>
<li>Create resources at the right level of granularity</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"IntroductiontoREST-WhatisaResource?">What is a Resource?</h3>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"133" src=3D"24756d318d98f70ceb0e2e1668ca07ed0bead77c05b1feb770929d9249=
22d404" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279299/image2021-11-22_=
13-22-21.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571073803&amp;api=3Dv2"=
 data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279300"=
 data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment=
" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-22_13-22-21.png" data-=
base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-con=
tent-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279299" da=
ta-linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" alt=3D"" width=3D"333"></span></=
p>
<p>Resources form the nucleus of any REST API design.<span>&nbsp;</span><sp=
an style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);" lang=3D"EN">Any information that can be =
named can be a resource: a document or image, a temporal service (e.g. "tod=
ay's weather in Los Angeles"), a collection of other resources, a non-virtu=
al object (e.g. a person), and so on.&nbsp;</span>It is very important to s=
elect the right resources and model the resources at the right granularity =
while designing the REST API so that the API consumers get the desired func=
tionality from the API's.</p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);" lang=3D"EN">The starting point in =
selection of resources is to analyse your business domain and extract the n=
ouns that are relevant to your business needs. More importantly, focus shou=
ld be given to the needs of API consumers and how to make the API relevant =
and useful from the perspective of API consumer interactions. Once the noun=
s (resources) have been identified, then the interactions with the API can =
be modelled as HTTP verbs against these nouns. When they don't map nicely, =
we could approximate. For example, we can easily use the =E2=80=9Cnouns in =
the domain=E2=80=9D approach and identify low level resources such as Post,=
 Tag, Comment, etc. in a blogging domain. Similarly, we can identify the no=
uns Customer, Address, Account, Teller, etc. as resources in a banking doma=
in.</span></p>
<p><strong>Further reading on what is a resource:</strong> <a href=3D"https=
://www.thoughtworks.com/insights/blog/rest-api-design-resource-modeling" st=
yle=3D"" rel=3D"nofollow" class=3D"external-link"><span style=3D"color: rgb=
(51,102,255);">https://www.thoughtworks.com/insights/blog/rest-api-design-r=
esource-modeling</span></a></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279302">Introduction to OpenAPI</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"994375ee-4ef4-42a9-911e-c52452d1=
d891-1203279302">
<h3 id=3D"IntroductiontoOpenAPI-WhatisOpenAPI?">What is OpenAPI?</h3>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"125" src=3D"c960f915e931c9a4590439c03a5c336bb669fed9cd42c43074387115ec=
22b465" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279302/OpenAPI-logo-sma=
ll.jpg?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1718172110767&amp;api=3Dv2" data-=
unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1721953120" data-=
linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data=
-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"OpenAPI-logo-small.jpg" data-base-url=3D"=
https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D=
"image/jpeg" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279302" data-linked-r=
esource-container-version=3D"4" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span><span class=
=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img =
class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" height=3D"175" src=
=3D"ce8bc9e2fd4b823d45124a7fb3c17061f5befbcac113f32eb9d09fa059dcf71b" data-=
image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279302/swagger-logo-horizontal.jpeg?=
version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571074233&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresol=
ved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279304" data-linked-=
resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked=
-resource-default-alias=3D"swagger-logo-horizontal.jpeg" data-base-url=3D"h=
ttps://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"=
image/jpeg" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279302" data-linked-re=
source-container-version=3D"4" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p>OpenAPI is a framework for describing your API using a common language t=
hat everyone can understand.</p>
<h3 id=3D"IntroductiontoOpenAPI-WhatisanOpenAPISpecification?">What is an O=
penAPI Specification?</h3>
<p>An OpenAPI Specification is a set of rules for a format describing REST =
APIs. The specification defines the interface of the API describing all sup=
ported resources, operations and expected responses in a format that makes =
it easier to develop and consume an API. It is an easy-to-learn, language a=
gnostic, and both human and machine readable</p>
<p><strong>Further reading: </strong><a href=3D"https://swagger.io/docs/spe=
cification/about/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://swagger=
.io/docs/specification/about/</a></p>
<h3 id=3D"IntroductiontoOpenAPI-BenefitsofOpenAPI">Benefits of OpenAPI</h3>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>It's comprehensible for deve=
lopers and non-developers.</strong>&nbsp;Product managers, partners, and ev=
en potential clients can have input into the design of your API, because th=
ey can see it clearly mapped out in this friendly UI.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>It's human readable&nbsp;<em=
>and</em>&nbsp;machine readable.</strong>&nbsp;This means that not only can=
 this be shared with your team internally, but the same documentation can b=
e used to automate API-dependent processes.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>It's easily adjustable</stro=
ng>. This makes it great for testing and debugging API problems.</span></li=
>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"IntroductiontoOpenAPI-OpenAPI(SwaggerV3)Support">OpenAPI (Swagger=
 V3) Support</h3>
<p>The Mesh Platform initially only had support for Swagger v2. This suppor=
t has now been extended to OpenAPI (Swagger v3.0.3), and is the recommended=
 contract specification for new Mesh APIs.</p>
<p>Existing APIs with a swagger specification will continue to be supported=
 in the Mesh.</p>
<p>The Mesh Design guidelines apply to both OpenAPI and Swagger contracts.<=
/p>
<h3 id=3D"IntroductiontoOpenAPI-TheGoldenTemplate">The Golden Template</h3>
<p>The golden swagger specifications are the template that all Westpac Mesh=
 API specifications are to use when designing a Westpac Mesh API. <strong>Y=
ou must always go to the repository and get the latest golden swagger speci=
fications whenever you are&nbsp; extending an API.&nbsp;</strong>Newly crea=
ted APIs will already&nbsp;be initialised with a sample swagger specificati=
on based on the latest golden template.</p>
<p>Whenever you extend an API you must ensure that any changes you make are=
 backwards compatible. This includes any changes you make when incorporatin=
g changes in the latest golden specification.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<ul>
<li>Changes to the information block are backwards compatible</li>
<li>Adding a new mandatory header field is not backwards compatible</li>
</ul>
<p>If changes cannot be made in a backwards compatible fashion then discuss=
 this with your architect, as a new major version may be required. <strong>=
Further reading</strong> -&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/MESH/API+Design+Standar=
ds#APIDesignStandards-versioning">API Design Standards#versioning</a></p>
<p>This repository contains the latest golden templates and some sample imp=
lementations. Please refer to the Readme.md for more information.</p>
<p><strong>Contract repository:</strong> <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D=
"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/contracts/browse"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/=
contracts/browse</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279307">Contract Guidelines</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"994375ee-4ef4-42a9-911e-c52452d1=
d891-1203279307">
<h3 id=3D"ContractGuidelines-APIInformation">API Information</h3>
<p>Basic information help others understand what functionality your API has=
. This information&nbsp;is displayed in Westpac Mesh Connect, so it is impo=
rtant in helping consumers discover your API.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"417" src=3D"f04b68a6ca0508fba234170209728982e032fb166f730b108b6c04a3d4=
415608" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279307/image2021-11-30_=
8-33-3.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571075013&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279312" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-30_8-33-3.png" data-base=
-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content=
-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279307" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"6" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<ul>
<li>Version: The version of your API. This follows <a href=3D"https://confl=
uence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/mesh/Versioning" rel=3D"nofollow">semantic=
 versioning</a>, and must be updated whenever changes are made to the API.<=
/li>
<li>Title: The display name of your API. This is typically determined durin=
g naming governance, and should closely match your API's shortname. eg. An =
API with name 'cap-technolsvcdsgndvlpmt-applnmgt-<em>meshcmpntmgt</em>-v1' =
should have 'Mesh Component Management' as the title.</li>
<li>Description: A high level business description of what your API does.</=
li>
<li>X-goldenVersion: The version number of the golden template your API is =
based on. When possible, this should always be kept in sync with the latest=
 Golden Template.</li>
<li>Host/basepath/schemes: These values should already be auto-generated, a=
nd should not be modified.</li>
<li>SecurityDefinitions: For non-proxy APIs, this should not be modified. A=
PIs on the internal gateway will communicate with basic authorisation.</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong>Parameters</strong></p>
<p>Your swagger will come with predefined mandatory headers that are used i=
nternally by Westpac Mesh. You typically should not modify these parameters=
, but feel free to add your own query/path parameters as required.&nbsp;</p=
>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> If using OpenAPI, these headers are automatically=
 injected for you at runtime, and you do not need to manually declare them.=
</p>
<p><strong><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embed=
ded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"fals=
e" height=3D"345" src=3D"25a6ff5063c4f0b362ef83139f0edc8ccbdb53f0589e0d4385=
f3721a4d5b28c5" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279307/image202=
1-11-30_8-54-39.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571074963&amp;ap=
i=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203=
279311" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"att=
achment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-30_8-54-39.png"=
 data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resour=
ce-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"12032793=
07" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"6" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></s=
pan></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>X-messageId: A GUID to represent a single transaction between a single =
component and another component on the platform. When implementing your API=
, this value should NOT be propogated.</li>
<li>X-appCorrelationId: A GUID to represent an end-to-end transaction, acro=
ss multiple components. This value should be propagated, Westpac Mesh provi=
ders <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDPCOM/repos/=
lib-westpac-digital-platform-wdp-helpers/browse" class=3D"external-link" re=
l=3D"nofollow">helper libraries</a> to assist with implementation.</li>
<li>X-organisationId: The organisation the caller is operating in. Note thi=
s is not the same as brand.</li>
<li>X-originatingSystemId: The Alfabet Id of the calling application</li>
<li>X-consumerType: The originating consumption channel invoking the API.</=
li>
<li>X-userId/X-userIdScheme: These should be used to identify the user invo=
king the API if required.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong>Paths</strong></p>
<p>Here you can define your resources/endpoints required by your API. Note =
that the GET /healthcheck is mandatory and should not be modified.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"367" src=3D"1cde2d6e251b1b25d9062ec7cb6f2a9c0981f9b5ff5932b8d6252fa36e=
95996c" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279307/image2021-11-30_=
9-14-58.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571074910&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279310" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-30_9-14-58.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279307" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"6" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<ul>
<li>Tags: This will appear as a title for your endpoint when viewed in the =
Swagger Editor.</li>
<li>OperationId: This will determine the name of the related classes when y=
ou generate code from your swagger.</li>
<li>Parameters: Mandatory headers will already be defined here. Feel free t=
o additional parameters more as required.</li>
<li>Responses: Here you can reference any defined response objects for each=
 HTTP error code.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ContractGuidelines-Responses">Responses</h3>
<p>Here you can define your response objects. Please note that HTTP 200 res=
ponses should ALWAYS have a 'data' object at the root level, which wraps yo=
ur response entity. At the root level, you may also have a 'paging' object.=
</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"242" src=3D"a6e4dc974e14972975ad370abccdbf04eddc0e8622f2c137599d44c3ee=
c0962a" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279307/image2021-11-30_=
9-27-39.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571074720&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279308" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-30_9-27-39.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279307" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"6" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>HTTP 400 and 500 error responses should list out all possible error code=
s and messages in their description. A table format should be used for ease=
 of reading.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"140" src=3D"d7d1c96aa5c57364f6b103f05e672203f628055b2a579d2e80c3854a81=
bcf68e" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279307/image2021-11-30_=
9-24-27.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571074803&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279309" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-30_9-24-27.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279307" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"6" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<h3 id=3D"ContractGuidelines-Definitions">Definitions</h3>
<p>Here you can define your response objects. You should write object defin=
itions with the intent of reuse across your swagger. Some other points to c=
onsider:</p>
<ul>
<li>Always include examples where possible. Ideally, examples should be at =
the field level, rather than the object level.</li>
<li>Pay attention to the naming of your definitions, as these your generate=
d classed will have the same names code is generating from the swagger.</li=
>
<li>Enums should not contain spaces, and have consistent casing</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ContractGuidelines-FurtherExamples">Further Examples</h3>
<p>You can find more examples in the <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westp=
ac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/contracts/browse/examples" class=3D"external-=
link" rel=3D"nofollow">Contracts repository</a> and in <a href=3D"https://m=
esh.westpac.com.au/components/apis" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow=
">Mesh Connect</a>, by searching for 'Reference Implementation'.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Sample OpenAPI contracts:</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/reference-scoped-=
access-v1?tab=3Dcontract" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://=
mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/reference-scoped-access-v1?tab=3Dcontra=
ct</a></p>
<p><a href=3D"https://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/mesh-component-qu=
ality-metrics-v2?tab=3Dcontract" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">h=
ttps://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/mesh-component-quality-metrics-v=
2?tab=3Dcontract</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Sample Swagger contracts:</p>
<p><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://mesh.westpac.com.au/component=
s/apis/inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-meshcmpnt-v1?tab=3Dcontract" rel=3D"=
nofollow">https://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/inf-bnkng-resrcitm-lo=
gclitcmpnt-meshcmpnt-v1?tab=3Dcontract</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279315">Proxy API Guidelines</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"994375ee-4ef4-42a9-911e-c52452d1=
d891-1203279315">
<p>Proxies are components that have an interface like an API, but do not co=
ntain any code implementation. They are used as passthroughs to actual APIs=
 that are on a separate host.&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77=
);">All outbound access to vendor service/&nbsp;API&nbsp; or an inbound acc=
ess by a partner is always through a proxy API that is hosted in Westpac Me=
sh API gateway .</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Vendor must supply a service speci=
fication/ contract in the form of Swagger / Open API definition (for Restfu=
l API's)&nbsp;or WSDL (for SOAP based Web services). The Proxy component al=
so should have</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.=
com.au/display/WDPIPAAS/Proxy+use+case+scenarios" rel=3D"nofollow">environm=
ent configuration and security policies</a>&nbsp;as per the&nbsp;<a href=3D=
"/display/MESH/Supported+Authentication">Supported Authentication</a></p>
<p>Different <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/=
repos/contracts/browse/examples" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">G=
olden Templates </a>are used for the different API Proxy use cases.</p>
<h3 id=3D"ProxyAPIGuidelines-ServiceProxy:OutboundaccesstoVendorAPI">Servic=
e Proxy: Outbound access to Vendor API</h3>
<p>For this use case where you need to consume either an external vendor AP=
I, or a non-Westpac Mesh internal API , you require a Service Proxy. Eg: MS=
 APIs / IBM Watson APIs etc&nbsp;</p>
<p>For a Service Proxy, you can use the <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.we=
stpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/contracts/browse/templates/swagger.yaml" c=
lass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Golden Template for a standard API<=
/a>, with the following considerations:</p>
<ul>
<li>As the resource definitions will follow what is specified in the vendor=
's API, the Proxy swagger does not need to strictly follow Westpac Mesh des=
ign guidelines. However some effort should be made to sanitise the swagger =
so it is readable and reusable for a broader audience.</li>
<li>x-headers which are mandatory for APIs running on Westpac Mesh can be r=
emoved. They should not be sent to external vendors. X-headers may be sent =
to non-Westpac Mesh internal APIs for logging/audit purposes.</li>
<li>'Vendor name' is suffixed to the title of the API to indicate it is a v=
endor Proxy&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p><map id=3D"gliffy-map-1203279319-2626" name=3D"gliffy-map-1203279319-262=
6"></map></p>
<table width=3D"100%" class=3D"gliffy-macro-table">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<table class=3D"gliffy-macro-inner-table">
<caption align=3D"bottom">
</caption>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><img style=3D"border: none; width: 836px;" usemap=3D"#gliffy-map-120327=
9319-2626" src=3D"e77ca5404b0e2d41f636d318ddbeaf2c1c68338b90a2733373f391999=
c49cf21" alt=3D"" class=3D"gliffy-macro-image" width=3D"468" height=3D"134"=
></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><strong>Further reading</strong> :=
&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"/display/MESH/Pattern+3%3A+Vendor+Supplied+API">Pat=
tern 3: Vendor Supplied API</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"ProxyAPIGuidelines-PartnerProxy:InboundaccesstoMeshAPI">Partner P=
roxy: Inbound access to Mesh API</h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">To expose our products and service=
s to partners that have an established relationship with the group we use P=
artner Proxies / APIs .</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&=
nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span>This is hosted on the External Partner Gateway. Eg=
: Parsifal / Open banking&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Partner APIs require two Swagger s=
pecifcations generally. One for the external gateway which our partners wil=
l see and one for the internal gateway which will reflect the additional he=
aders injected by the external gateway.<span> With the Simplified Partner P=
roxy pattern, you only need a single repository with one Swagger specificat=
ion. The additional configuration required for the external proxy will be c=
reated automatically.</span></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">The external GW interface is just =
a proxy and the internal partner is a Java API.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><map id=3D"gliffy-map-1212885420-4673" name=3D"gliffy-map-1212885420-467=
3"></map></p>
<table width=3D"100%" class=3D"gliffy-macro-table">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<table class=3D"gliffy-macro-inner-table">
<caption align=3D"bottom">
</caption>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><img style=3D"border: none; width: 1100px;" usemap=3D"#gliffy-map-12128=
85420-4673" src=3D"13cdfa0951fe1135d4c0b367120b07ff0d49b3ab838c8e7b757ebf21=
961838b6" alt=3D"" class=3D"gliffy-macro-image" width=3D"468" height=3D"157=
"></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><strong>Further reading:</strong> =
<a href=3D"/display/MD/Simplify+Partner+Proxy">Simplify Partner Proxy</a></=
span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>The Partner Proxy swagger should be <span style=3D"color: rgb(32,33,36);=
">analogous&nbsp;</span>to that of the internal API. The key difference tha=
t the Partner Proxy swagger will be based on the <a href=3D"https://bitbuck=
et.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/contracts/browse/templates/swagge=
r-partner.yaml" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Partner Proxy Gold=
en Template</a>.</p>
<ul>
<li>SecurityDefinitions will need be set for the External Partner Proxy.</l=
i>
<li>Certain mandatory headers such as&nbsp;x-originatingSystemId and x-cons=
umerType, are injected by the gateway, and can be removed from the External=
 Partner Proxy's swagger. Tracing headers x-messageId and x-appCorrelationI=
d can be passed through by the Partner if required.</li>
<li>If the interface is driven by Westpac , then the Proxy will also adhere=
 adhere to Westpac Mesh guidelines.&nbsp;</li>
<li>If the interface is provided by the vendor / follow an industry standar=
d such as open banking&nbsp; then it will conform to their standards&nbsp;<=
/li>
<li>The External Partner Proxy will be defined as agreed upon by the Partne=
r and development team. This Proxy does not necessarily need to follow West=
pac Mesh guidelines, but should still be based on the Partner Proxy Golden =
Template.</li>
<li>The Internal Partner Proxy will mirror the swagger of the External Part=
ner Proxy, but will contain code for transforming the incoming request to m=
atch the specifications of the internal API.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ProxyAPIGuidelines-ConfiguringyourProxy">Configuring your Proxy</=
h3>
<p>You can read more about how to configure your Proxy API at the below lin=
k.</p>
<p><strong>Further reading:</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong><a href=3D"/display/MESH/Proxy+use+case+scenarios">Proxy use cas=
e scenarios</a></strong></p>
<p><strong><a href=3D"/display/MESH/API+Naming+Standards#APINamingStandards=
-Exposinginternalapplicationout-of-the-boxAPIsorWSDLstoPartners">API Naming=
 Standards#Exposinginternalapplicationout-of-the-boxAPIsorWSDLstoPartners</=
a></strong></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279324">Exercise: Getting started editing a Swagger spec=
ification</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"994375ee-4ef4-42a9-911e-c52452d1=
d891-1203279324">
<p>As a Designer, you should be comfortable editing a Swagger specification=
. Note that while the Golden Template is typically auto-populated for you w=
hen creating a project, for the purposes of this exercise, we will attempt =
to fill in the Swagger ourselves.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>First, let's open the <a href=3D"https://swagger.mesh.westpac.com.au/" c=
lass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Swagger Editor</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Note</strong>: Westpac has hosted Swagger Editor internally. The=
 link above is the internal one. DO NOT use the one available in internet&n=
bsp;</p>
<p>In another window, find the Swagger Golden Template in the <a href=3D"ht=
tps://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/contracts/browse" cl=
ass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">contracts repository</a>. The Readme=
.md should give you some indication on where to find this if you are stuck.=
</p>
<p>Open the file, copy and paste the contents into the Swagger Editor. You =
should see an error as below:</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"225" src=3D"bcc7f31c695928694d161a59e2ed3df2c56dec6b0b34238d9cafeaa8bb=
f19423" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279324/image2021-11-30_=
19-53-37.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571077357&amp;api=3Dv2"=
 data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279332"=
 data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment=
" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-30_19-53-37.png" data-=
base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-con=
tent-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279324" da=
ta-linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></=
p>
<p>We are seeing errors, because the template has not been populated yet. W=
e want to replace the braces&nbsp;{{ }} with some meaningful data.</p>
<ul>
<li>Update the version to: 1.0.0</li>
<li>Update the title to: Board Game Retrieval</li>
<li>Update the description to: This API retrieves a list of board games and=
 their details.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>This should get rid of the error. Now let's do some basic editing.</p>
<p>Scroll down to the first resource.</p>
<ul>
<li>Update /sampleResources to /boardGames</li>
<li>Update the tag to: Retrieve Board Games List</li>
<li>Remove the brandSilo parameter</li>
</ul>
<p>The right hand side of the screen should update with your new details to=
 look something like below:</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"276" src=3D"19eb8ed8a58638cc07538960823f819b6656cc063aaefd680b628badc1=
1cc5d3" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279324/image2021-11-30_=
20-6-59.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571077307&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279331" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-30_20-6-59.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279324" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p>Now let's edit the response object.&nbsp;Note the the response objects a=
re all references as denoted by <strong>$ref</strong>.</p>
<p>Let's find the response object for a HTTP 200. Hit Ctrl+F and Search for=
&nbsp;200GetSampleResourceListResponse.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"150" src=3D"dc22ca90efd20423e45d2f9eb8aa3c12f1dae64f7f04a9a0114d3725c1=
78052e" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279324/image2021-11-30_=
20-8-35.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571077257&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279330" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-30_20-8-35.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279324" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p>Notice how the schema of&nbsp;200GetSampleResourceListResponse contains =
two attributes:</p>
<ul>
<li>data: this is object is mandatory, and expected for all HTTP 200 respon=
ses. You can define the contents of your response object in here.</li>
<li>paging: an optional object we can use to describe the subset of data th=
at we are viewing when we have a large result set. We will learn more about=
 paging later.</li>
</ul>
<p>Let's make some updates to this object.</p>
<ul>
<li>Update the name of the array to boardGames</li>
<li>Delete the example block that you find under the 200GetSampleResourceLi=
stResponse object. It is easier to maintain your examples by setting them a=
t the field level.</li>
</ul>
<p>Again, notice how the right side has updated (you might need to scroll d=
own to find the response example).</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"398" src=3D"a052e13e74e183d728d9519784222da8ed7eb9e8cb0a13aeba3603a267=
86658b" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279324/image2021-11-30_=
20-29-18.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571077090&amp;api=3Dv2"=
 data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279327"=
 data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment=
" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-30_20-29-18.png" data-=
base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-con=
tent-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279324" da=
ta-linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></=
p>
<p>The elements of the array are defined by&nbsp;SampleResourceList. Search=
 for this object and edit the fields with some examples.</p>
<ul>
<li>Update id with an example. Underneath the description line, add: exampl=
e: "123". Note that quotes are required, as the example could be incorrectl=
y interpreted as a numeric.</li>
<li>Update name with an example.</li>
</ul>
<p>You should see something like below:</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"377" src=3D"07c227d3384b2a30412f1fd83f02806375d4b9ecdd0c8f813d47dc4546=
fedf59" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279324/image2021-11-30_=
20-45-45.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571076927&amp;api=3Dv2"=
 data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279326"=
 data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment=
" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-11-30_20-45-45.png" data-=
base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-con=
tent-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279324" da=
ta-linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></=
p>
<p>Finally, using what you have learned, see if you can update the 400 erro=
r codes to look something like the below:</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"206" src=3D"2f33b69472c81e3bf487f6d0e140c278101d7ce568387d8cdb9c5324da=
